ne aminotransferase, <italic>Bi</italic> bilirubin, <italic>GGT</italic> gamma-glutamyl transpeptidase, <italic>AST/ALT</italic> aspartate aminotransferase/alanine aminotransferase ratio, <italic>FI</italic> Forns fibrosis index, <italic>APRI</italic> AST to platelet ratio index.</p></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap><p>In patients who lost between 5-10% of baseline weight (n =17, 29.3%) there was an improved GGT, alkaline phosphatase, Forns index, and APRI (Table&#x000a0;<xref ref-type="table" rid="T6">6</xref>).</p><p>In patients from NGLCD group who have lost more than 10% of the body weight (n&#x02009;=&#x02009;6) there was a significant improvement of non-invasive index of liver fibrosis (Forns index) (Table&#x000a0;<xref ref-type="table" rid="T6">6</xref>).</p></sec><sec><title>In LFD patients group</title><p>In patients with weight gain (n&#x02009;=&#x02009;4, 7.7%) we observed a slight improvement of Forns index, probably obtained in the context of reduced fat consumption (Table&#x000a0;<xref ref-type="table" rid="T7">7</xref>).</p><table-wrap position="float" id="T7"><label>Table 7</label><caption><p>Groups of weight loss and liver function parameters in patients with LFD</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups" border="1"><colgroup><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/><col align="left"/></colgroup><thead valign="top"><tr><th align="left" valign="bottom">&#x000a0;<hr/></th><th align="left" valign="bottom">&#x000a0;<hr/></th><th colspan="2" align="left" valign="bottom"><bold>Weight gain</bold><hr/></th><th colspan="2" align="left" valign="bottom"><bold>1-5% weight loss</bold><hr/></th><th colspan="2" align="left" valign="bottom"><bold>5-10% weight loss</bold><hr/></th><th colspan="2" align="left" valign="bottom"><bold>Weight loss &#x0003e;10%</bold><hr/></th><th align="left" valign="bottom"><bold>p</bol